
                     T H E   L A S T   E I C H H O F           

Original version Alpha-Helix 1993.
Ported to Allegro library Gavin Smith 2014.

This repo is forked from loonycyborg's repo and minor fixes by WildPenguin 2026.

INSTALLATION

On a Unix-like system, run ./configure followed by make install.High score and
config will be put in user home directory (according to XDG_CONFIG_HOME or 
HOME variables, most probably in $HOME/.config/lastbeer).

If you want a global configuration and high score file, comment out the relevant
line in Makefile.am.

You need Allegro 4, on Debian derivatives it comes as liballegro4-dev.

KNOWN ISSUES

This game uses Allegro 4. That library is ancient and unmaintained (Allegro5 is 
active).

Especially when playing on Wayland, fullscreen doesn't work properly. The game
has trouble registering keystrokes (no problems under X.Org). Fullscreen will
also be stretched on non 4:3, as the game (currently) just takes whatever 
Allegro4 thinks is the best resolution.

Workarounds:
- start with /SX to scale the game window. You can then yse your window manager 
  to get the window borderless (and effectively fullscreen) or just play
  in a larger window according to your preference.
- The intro screen scale can be set with /ISX.
- You can use float values for scaling (albeit integers will look best)
- Use gamescope. Something like `-S integer -F pixel` get the results I like
  most, but you might prefer something else. There may be slight graphical
  slowdowns with gamescope (like the price decrement in the shop). Set in-game
  scale to 1 if you use Gamescope as it will do it's own scaling!

TODO: Instead set a fullscreen resolution, it's much more user friendly. Ask the 
user for a windows size. As ffor Intro, don't resize but fit the intro into the
desired game window.

TODO: Port to Allegro 5 =)

The game uses 320 x 240 (scales nicely to 640 x 480) but the intro uses 
640 x 350. These are both old VGA/EGA resolutions. 640 x 350 probably didn't
have a square PAR originally.

